Here's a clean implementation using `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (the recommended approach for .NET MAUI):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace YourApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isBusy;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        if (IsBusy) return;

        try
        {
            IsBusy = true;

            // Replace with your actual data service call
            await Task.Delay(500);
            var product = await FetchProductAsync();

            Name = product.Name;
            Price = product.Price;
            IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsBusy = false;
        }
    }

    private Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        // Simulated fetch — swap in your real service
        return Task.FromResult(("Widget Pro", 29.99m, true));
    }
}
```

**How it works:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` — source-generates the public property with `INotifyPropertyChanged` support (e.g., `_name` → `Name`).
- `[RelayCommand]` — generates `LoadCommand` (an `IAsyncRelayCommand`) from `LoadAsync`, which automatically disables re-entry during execution.
- `IsBusy` lets you bind an `ActivityIndicator`.

**XAML usage:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsBusy}" />
        <Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

Install the toolkit via NuGet: `dotnet add package CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`.
